WorkItem.Description:
It's part of the spec http://xhr.spec.whatwg.org/#xmlhttprequest and of some implementations (at least current stable Firefox and Chrome)

Test case that makes the compiler raise an error:

var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();

if (xhr.overrideMimeType) {
    xhr.overrideMimeType('text/plain; charset=utf-8');
}

> error TS2094: The property 'overrideMimeType' does not exist on value of type 'XMLHttpRequest'.

inspired from https://github.com/fabi1cazenave/webL10n/blob/b18c753c6fe81e733d86660d421ace7a7880e90f/l10n.js#L124-L127
